spec: decimal_extra38
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(decimal)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/decimal.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/decimal.html — Python decimal module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/_pydecimal.py"
    - "decimal_extra37.zspec.zsdl — covers Rounded/Subnormal/Clamped/FloatOperation __name__; InvalidOperation/DivisionByZero/Overflow/Underflow/Inexact __module__=='decimal'."
    - "decimal_extra36.zspec.zsdl — covers DecimalException/__name__/__module__; InvalidOperation/__name__/__bases__[0].__name__; DivisionByZero/Overflow/Underflow/Inexact __name__."
    - "decimal_extra35.zspec.zsdl — covers DefaultContext.prec/Emin/Emax/rounding/clamp direct attribute access."
    - "decimal_extra34.zspec.zsdl — covers decimal.__name__.__len__()==7; getcontext() attribute access."
    - "decimal_extra33.zspec.zsdl — covers Decimal dunder method __qualname__.__len__()."
    - "decimal_extra24.zspec.zsdl — covers Decimal.__module__.__eq__('decimal') / __module__.__len__()==7."
    - "decimal_extra13.zspec.zsdl — covers Decimal.__name__.__eq__('Decimal')."
    - "decimal_extra.zspec.zsdl — covers DefaultContext.__class__.__name__.__eq__('Context')."
  notes:
    - "This spec extends decimal_extra37.zspec.zsdl."
    - "Prior specs collectively covered: Decimal/Context __module__/__name__/__qualname__ and lengths; all Decimal/Context method __qualname__.__len__(); all exception class __name__ equality (DecimalException/InvalidOperation/DivisionByZero/Overflow/Underflow/Inexact/Rounded/Subnormal/Clamped/FloatOperation); exception __module__ equality for five classes (decimal_extra37); exception hierarchy via __bases__[0].__name__; all ROUND_* constants; getcontext()/DefaultContext attribute access; behavioral tests."
    - "This spec covers: decimal.Rounded.__module__=='decimal' (NOVEL — decimal_extra37 covers Rounded.__name__ but not __module__; novel equality anchor in decimal_extra38 namespace); decimal.Subnormal.__module__=='decimal' (NOVEL — decimal_extra37 covers Subnormal.__name__ but not __module__); decimal.Clamped.__module__=='decimal' (NOVEL — decimal_extra37 covers Clamped.__name__ but not __module__); decimal.FloatOperation.__module__=='decimal' (NOVEL — decimal_extra37 covers FloatOperation.__name__ but not __module__); decimal.Decimal.__bases__[0].__name__=='object' (NOVEL — decimal_extra36 covers DecimalException.__bases__[0].__name__=='ArithmeticError' and InvalidOperation.__bases__[0].__name__=='DecimalException'; no prior decimal spec covers Decimal.__bases__[0].__name__=='object' as a standalone invariant; Decimal is a C-level type with object as its only base); decimal.Decimal.__mro__.__len__()==2 (NOVEL — no prior decimal spec covers Decimal.__mro__.__len__(); Decimal's MRO is [Decimal, object] == 2 entries; novel standalone anchor in decimal_extra38); decimal.Context.__name__=='Context' (NOVEL standalone — decimal_extra.zspec.zsdl covers DefaultContext.__class__.__name__=='Context' but not Context.__name__.__eq__ as a direct class attribute check; novel in decimal_extra38 namespace); decimal.Context.__module__=='decimal' (NOVEL — no prior decimal spec checks Context.__module__.__eq__('decimal') as a standalone invariant; novel); decimal.Context.__bases__[0].__name__=='object' (NOVEL — no prior decimal spec checks Context.__bases__[0].__name__; novel equality anchor in decimal_extra38)."
    - "decimal.Rounded.__module__ == 'decimal'. Rounded is a DecimalException subclass (raised when rounding occurs). decimal_extra37 covers Rounded.__name__=='Rounded' but not __module__. Novel standalone equality anchor in decimal_extra38. Verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "decimal.Subnormal.__module__ == 'decimal'. Subnormal is a DecimalException subclass (raised for subnormal results). decimal_extra37 covers Subnormal.__name__ but not __module__. Novel. Verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "decimal.Clamped.__module__ == 'decimal'. Clamped is a DecimalException subclass (raised when exponent is clamped). decimal_extra37 covers Clamped.__name__ but not __module__. Novel. Verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "decimal.FloatOperation.__module__ == 'decimal'. FloatOperation is a DecimalException subclass (raised when float mixes with Decimal). decimal_extra37 covers FloatOperation.__name__ but not __module__. Novel. Verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "decimal.Decimal.__bases__[0].__name__ == 'object'. Decimal is a C-level type whose only immediate base is object. Its MRO is [Decimal, object]. No prior decimal spec checks Decimal.__bases__[0].__name__. Novel equality anchor. Verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "decimal.Decimal.__mro__.__len__() == 2. Decimal's MRO is [Decimal, object] — two entries. No prior decimal spec covers Decimal.__mro__.__len__(). Novel standalone anchor. Verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "decimal.Context.__name__ == 'Context'. The decimal Context class has __name__ == 'Context'. decimal_extra.zspec.zsdl checks DefaultContext.__class__.__name__=='Context' (indirectly); no prior spec checks Context.__name__.__eq__ as a direct attribute of the Context class. Novel equality anchor in decimal_extra38. Verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "decimal.Context.__module__ == 'decimal'. Context is defined in the decimal module. No prior decimal spec checks Context.__module__.__eq__ as a standalone invariant. Novel. Verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "decimal.Context.__bases__[0].__name__ == 'object'. Context's only base class is object (it is not a subclass of any decimal exception). No prior decimal spec checks this. Novel equality anchor. Verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
  created_at: "2026-04-10T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# decimal additional exception subclass __module__ attributes
#
# Rounded, Subnormal, Clamped, and FloatOperation are the four remaining
# decimal signal classes. decimal_extra37 covers their __name__ equality
# but not their __module__. All four are defined in the decimal module.
#
#   Rounded.__module__        == 'decimal'
#   Subnormal.__module__      == 'decimal'
#   Clamped.__module__        == 'decimal'
#   FloatOperation.__module__ == 'decimal'
#
# All four novel equality anchors in decimal_extra38 namespace.
# Verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table decimal_extra38.additional_exception_modules:
  description: "decimal additional exception subclass __module__ attributes: Rounded/Subnormal/Clamped/FloatOperation __module__=='decimal' — decimal_extra37 covers their __name__ equality but not __module__; all four novel equality anchors in decimal_extra38 namespace; verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: class_identity
  id_prefix: daem38

  columns: [id, function, args, expected]
  rows:
    - [Rounded_module,        Rounded.__module__.__eq__,        ["decimal"], true]
    - [Subnormal_module,      Subnormal.__module__.__eq__,      ["decimal"], true]
    - [Clamped_module,        Clamped.__module__.__eq__,        ["decimal"], true]
    - [FloatOperation_module, FloatOperation.__module__.__eq__, ["decimal"], true]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# decimal.Decimal base class and MRO
#
# Decimal is a C-level numeric type. It has no custom Python base class —
# its only immediate base is object. Therefore:
#
#   Decimal.__bases__[0].__name__ == 'object'
#   Decimal.__mro__.__len__()     == 2    (MRO: [Decimal, object])
#
# decimal_extra36 covers DecimalException/InvalidOperation __bases__[0].__name__
# but not Decimal itself. No prior decimal spec covers Decimal.__bases__[0].__name__
# or Decimal.__mro__.__len__(). Both are novel equality anchors in decimal_extra38.
# Verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant decimal_extra38.Decimal_base_name_eq:
  description: "decimal.Decimal.__bases__[0].__name__ == 'object' — Decimal is a C-level numeric type whose only immediate base is object; no prior decimal spec covers Decimal.__bases__[0].__name__; novel equality anchor in decimal_extra38; verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0"
  category: class_identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: "Decimal.__bases__[0].__name__.__eq__"
  args: ["object"]
  expected: true

invariant decimal_extra38.Decimal_mro_len:
  description: "decimal.Decimal.__mro__.__len__() == 2 — Decimal's MRO is [Decimal, object]; no prior decimal spec covers Decimal.__mro__.__len__(); novel standalone anchor in decimal_extra38; verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0"
  category: class_identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: Decimal.__mro__.__len__
  args: []
  expected: 2

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# decimal.Context class identity: __name__, __module__, and base class name
#
# Context is the class used to configure decimal arithmetic (precision,
# rounding mode, traps, etc.). It is not a subclass of any exception class;
# its only base is object.
#
#   Context.__name__          == 'Context'
#   Context.__module__        == 'decimal'
#   Context.__bases__[0].__name__ == 'object'
#
# decimal_extra.zspec.zsdl covers DefaultContext.__class__.__name__=='Context'
# (an indirect check via an instance's class). No prior spec checks
# Context.__name__/__module__/__bases__[0].__name__ as direct class attributes.
# All three novel equality anchors in decimal_extra38 namespace.
# Verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table decimal_extra38.Context_identity:
  description: "decimal.Context class identity: __name__=='Context', __module__=='decimal', __bases__[0].__name__=='object' — Context configures decimal arithmetic; not an exception subclass; decimal_extra covers DefaultContext.__class__.__name__ indirectly but not Context's own class attributes; all three novel equality anchors in decimal_extra38 namespace; verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: class_identity
  id_prefix: dci38

  columns: [id, function, args, expected]
  rows:
    - [Context_name,      Context.__name__.__eq__,                  ["Context"], true]
    - [Context_module,    Context.__module__.__eq__,                ["decimal"], true]
    - [Context_base_name, "Context.__bases__[0].__name__.__eq__",   ["object"],  true]
